column5: THANKS AGAIN FOR ANOTHER GREAT EVENT>>   THE PRIZES WERE GREAT,   THE DOUBLE BURGERS VERY YUMMY.. COULD'NT FISH INNISFIL BUT BETTER SAFE THAN SORRY  CANT WAIT UNTIL NEXT YEAR  DAVE
Was there a good crowd there Dave ?

Ditto  For those that provided prizes, auction items, the bidders, organized and attended, you have an open invitation on my boat anytime. PM me if you'd like to get out on LO for salmon/rainbow.  Simon
Simon, you are a true gent my friend  A big thanks goes out to you and jim
I think the weather kept some people away today.  All I know is that it was a fun day for a good cause. Met good folks and went home happy.
Was great seeing all of you again. As always it was a blast. My little girl had fun even if the fish didn't cooperate this year.
Glad to hear those who went had a good time, despite the wind and lack of good ice. I'm sorry I couldn't get there this year...  Maureen

There was a good crowd again this year but it was down from previous years, I do think the weather and lack of ice was a big factor but none the less, for those that went it was fun as usual! It was really nice to see many of the old faces and have a chance to catch up. I did miss some of the regulars that couldn't make it this year but hopefully next year.
